summary: The ninth full-length studio release from Demi Lovato was executive produced by Zhone.
The first full-length release from British pop singer-songwriter Lily Allen in seven years about the collapse of a marriage was created over 16 days.

The five disc (4 CDs and 1 Blu-ray) release from Bruce Springsteen features a remaster of the 192 album, 15 previously unreleased tracks including the Electric Nebraska sessions, home recordings and a solo studio session. A live performance filmed 2025 at New Jersey's Count Basie Theatre by Thom Zimny is on the Blu-ray disc.
The first full-length studio release from Chicago's Tortoise since 2016's The Catastrophist was recorded in Chicago, Los Aneles and Portland, Oregon.

The first full-length release of original songs from The Lemonheads since 2006's self-titled album features contributions by Bryce Goggin, The Moldy Peaches' Adam Green, Juliana Hatfield, J Mascis, Tom Morgan, Erin Rae, The Bevis Frond's Nick Saloman, and John Strohm of the Blake Babies.
The latest full-length solo release from singer-songwriter Brandi Carlile was produced with Aaron Dessner, Justin Vernon and Andrew Watt.
The third full-length release from Irish rock band Just Mustard was self-produced and was mixed by David Wrench.
The second full-length release from New York-based pop singer-songwriter Hannah Jadagu was co-produced with Sora Lopez and Max Baby.
The latest full-length release from Kevin Parker's music project Tame Impala is said to be inspired by "bush doof culture and the Western Australia rave scene."
The second full-length release from British rock The Last Dinner Party was produce by Markus Dravs.
The latest full-length release from violinist Sudan Archives features influences from club music and was recorded in Chicago, Detroit and Los Angeles.
The first full-length studio release in seven years from Belgian electronic band Soulwax was created using only modular synths, live drums, tape machines, and processed vocals.
The latest full-length release from London-based rock trio bar italia was recorded in Mexico City and was self-produced.
The second full-length release from Los Angeles punk band Militarie Gun features songs co-written with such artists as James Goodson of Dazy, Phillip Odom, and Nick Panella of MSPAINT.

album_title: Tower Block In A Jam Jar
summary: The sixth full-length release from British indie pop band Mozart Estate - who were previously known as Go-Kart Mozart - features new re-recordings of songs from Go-Kart Mozart's 2005 album, Tearing Up The Album Charts.

album_title: And Your Song Is Like A Circle
summary: The second full-length release from New York indie-folk artist Skullcrusher was produced with apob and Isaac Eiger.

artist_name: by They Are Gutting A Body Of Water
summary: The fourth full-length studio release (it's first on the ATO label) from Philadelphia shoegaze band that began as a solo project for frontman Douglas Dulgarian was self-produced.
Consumerism and the rapid destruction of nature are some of the themes on the latest release from the Peter Silberman-led indie rock band, The Antlers.

The latest full-length release from British electronic duo The Orb features contributions from Andy Caine, Roger Eno, Andy Falconer, Paul Ferguson, Miquette Giraudy, Steve Hillage, Violetta Vicci, Eric Von Skywalker, Trevor Walters, and Youth.
The latest full-length release from indie artist Jay Som features guest appearances by Jimmy Eat World's Jim Adkins and Paramore's Hayley Williams.
The second full-length release from British electronic producer Blawan features a guest appearance by Monstera Black.
The latest full-length release from Nashville-based singer-songwriter Madi Diaz was produced with Gabe Wax.
The debut full-length release from Los Angeles rock quartet Rocket was produced and mixed by band guitarist Desi Scaglione.

album_title: A Lifetime Of Riding By Night
summary: The latest full-length solo release from Old 97's Rhett Miller features a guest appearance by Evan Felker of Turnpike Troubadours and was produced by Old 97's Murry Hammond. It was recorded before he underwent surgery to remove a cyst and a polyp on his vocal cords.

album_title: In The Wind Of Night, Hard-Fallen Incantations Whisper
summary: This is the latest full-length release from Slovenian self-described "imaginary folk" trio Širom.
The latest release from Mexican duo Lorelle Meets the Obsolete features contributions by Alvaro Castro.
The three-disc release from Australian trio The Necks features one track over an hour long and another at just over 57 minutes (plus two over 25-minute-long tracks).

artist_name: by St. Paul & the Broken Bones
summary: The latest full-length release from Alabama soul group St. Paul & The Broken Bones was produced by Eg White.
The third full-length release from the collaboration between Brian Eno and Beatie Wolfe is said to sound like the hybrid of their two previous albums, Lateral and Luminal, released in June.
The third full-length release from Jenn Wasner's solo project Flock Of Dimes was recorded in Chapel Hill, North Carolina and Los Angeles, California.

album_title: The Besnard Lakes Are The Ghost Nation
summary: The latest full-length release from Montreal psychedelic rock band The Besnard Lakes was produced by band co-founders Jace Lasek and Olga Goreas.
The second full-length release from Vermont singer-songwriter Hannah Frances features a guest appearance by Grizzly Bear's Daniel Rossen (who also co-produced).

album_title: Once Upon A Time... In Shropshire
summary: This is the second full-length solo release from composer Jerskin Fendrix, who is best known for his score for Yorgos Lanthimos' 2003 film, "Poor Things."

Produced by Sean Ono Lennon, the 12-disc (nine CDs and three Blu-ray discs) box set includes 31 newly remixed tracks from both the afternoon and evening One To One Concerts at Madison Square Garden on 30 August 1972 featuring John Lennon and Yoko Ono with Elephant's Memory; a newly remixed version of 1972's Sometime In New York City; an audio documentary about the making of the tracks on New York City; 33 tracks of home recording; 27 live tracks; and a 204-page book.
The latest full-length solo release from California singer-songwriter Madison Cunningham features a guest appearance by Fleet Foxes' Robin Pecknold.
The latest full-length release from Taylor Swift features a guest appearance by Sabrina Carpenter and was produced with Max Martin and Shellback.
The latest full-length release from California rock quartet AFI was produced by band guitarist Jade Puget.
The second full-length release from Los Angeles-based black metal band Agriculture features a guest appearance by Emma Ruth Rundle.
The second full-length release from the Nashville punk band Snooper was produced by John Congleton.
The latest full-length release from Northern Irish pop rock band Ash features a guest appearance by Graham Coxon.
The latest full-length release from the Scottish indie rock quintet Idlewild was produced by band guitarist Rod Jones.
The eight-track collection of previously unreleased covers songs by Waylon Jennings recorded between 1973 and 1984 was mixed and selected by his son, Shooter Jennings.
The second full-length solo release from British singer-songwriter Dodie features a guest appearance by Greta Isaac.
The latest full-length solo release from The Verve's Richard Ashcroft features a guest appearance by Mirwais.
The latest full-length release from Los Angeles artist Doja Cat features a guest appearance by SZA.
The first full-length studio release from Mariah Carey since 2018's Caution features guest appearances by Anderson .Paak, Kehlani, Shenseea, and The Clark Sisters.
Wilco's Jeff Tweedy's 30-track solo release features contributions by Sima Cunningham, James Elkington, Liam Kazar, Macie Stewart, and his sons Sammy and Spencer Tweedy.
The latest full-length release from Led Zeppelin's Robert Plant features vocals from Suzi Dian, and contributions by Oli Jefferson, Tony Kelsey, Barney Morse-Brown, and Matt Worley.
The latest full-length release from Welsh singer-songwriter Cate Le Bon features a guest appearance by John Cale.
The first full-length solo studio release since 2018's Hell-On from singer-songwriter Neko Case was self-produced.
The latest full-length release from Brooklyn rock band Geese was produced with Kenneth Blume (formerly known as Kenny Beats).
The second full-length release from Irish post-punk band Sprints was produced by Gilla Band's Daniel Fox.
The second full-length release from British soul-pop artist Olivia Dean was executive produced by Zach Nahome.
The four-track release from Chicago instrumental trio Bitchin Bajas was self-recorded and mixed.

The latest full-length release from Canadian indie pop artist Patrick Watson features duets with Charlotte Cardin, Hohnen Ford, La Force, MARO, November Ultra, Klô Pelgag, Sea Oleena, Solann, and Martha Wainwright.
The latest full-length release from Swedish pop artist Zara Larsson features contributions by Helena Gao, Margo XS, MNEK, and Zhone.
The latest full-length release from Canadian power pop band Sloan was produced and mixed with Ryan Haslett.
The latest full-length release from Ethiopian jazz artist Mulatu Astatke was produced by Dexter Story and features contributions by Kibrom Birhane and Carlos Niño.
The latest full-length solo release from singer-songwriter Amanda Shires was produced by Lawrence Rothman.
A video game soundtrack is the concept behind Purity Ring's fourth full-length release.
The latest full-length release from Canadian artist Rochelle Jordan includes producing by Rob Araujo, Byron The Aquarius, DāM FunK, Initial Talk, KAYTRANADA, KLSH, and Machinedrum.

album_title: The Lamb Lies Down On Broadway [50th Anniversary Super Deluxe Edition]
summary: The 1974 album from British progressive rock band Genesis is remastered by Miles Showell for a Super Deluxe edition that features the complete recording of the band's January 24, 1975 performance at Los Angeles' Shrine Auditorium; a Blu-ray disc with the Dolby ATMOS mix of the album overseen by Peter Gabriel and Tony Banks; and a download for three previously unreleased demos from the Headley Grange Sessions. It also includes a reproduction of the 1975 tour program, a replica ticket, poster and a 60-page book.
The latest full-length release from saxophonist Donny McCaslin was recorded with Zach Danziger, Jason Linder, Tim Lefevbre (who also produced), Ben Monder, and Nate Wood.
The debut full-length release from Scottish indie pop duo The Cords was recorded over six days with Jonny Scott.

album_title: Begging The Night To Take Hold
summary: The first full-length solo release from The Delgados former singer Emma Pollock in nine years was recorded over five years.
The second full-length release from Sons of Kemet co-founder Tom Skinner features contributions by Contour, Meshell Ndegeocello, Portishead's Adrian Utley, and Yaffra.

The latest full-length release from rapper Young Thug features guest appearances by 1300SAINT, 21 Savage, Cardi B, Ken Carson, Future, Lil Baby, Lil Gotit, Mariah the Scientist, Travis Scott, Sexyy Red, T.I., and YFN Lucci
The latest full-length release from Kentucky rock trio White Reaper was self-produced.

The second full-length studio release from rapper Cardi B features guest appearances by  Cash Cobain, Selena Gomez, Janet Jackson, Kehlani, Lizzo, Lourdiz, Megan Thee Stallion, Tyla, and Summer Walker.
The latest full-length release from North Carolina rock band Wednesday was produced by Alex Farrar.
The first full-length studio release since 2019's Office Politics from Neil Hannon-led band The Divine Comedy was recorded at Abbey Road Studios.
The debut full-length collaboration between Four Tet's Kieran Hebden and William Tyler was recorded in Los Angles and Nashville.

Before joining Fleetwood Mac, Stevie Nicks and Lindsey Buckingham released their only album as a duo in 1973. The reissued album is remastered from the original analog master tapes and released on CD for the first time.
The latest full-length release from British singer-songwriter Lola Young features contributions by Carter Lang, Manuka, and Solomonophonic.
The second full-length release from London-based Irish trio NewDad was produced by Shrink.
The soundtrack for third film in the TRON franchise is the first film soundtrack from Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross under the Nine Inch Nails name.
The latest full-length release from Scottish trio Biffy Clyro was produced with Jonathan Gilmore, who also mixed the album.
The latest full-length release from jazz artist Cécile McLorin Salvant features guest appearances by Kate Davis and June McDoom.
The second full-length release from British singer-songwriter Joy Crookes features guest appearances by Sam Fender, Kano and Vince Staples.

The sixth and final studio release from British rock band Cardiacs was originally planned for a 2008 release when frontman Tim Smith suffered a heart attack and stroke. Work on the album continued after his death in 2020 with contributions from such artists as Duncan "The Honest Man" Cooper, Jon "The Choirboy" Daniel, Shane Embury, Nick Howiantz, Emily Freya Jones, Steve Morricone, Mick Pugh, and Yael Claire Shahmoon.
The latest full-length release from Canadian singer-songwriter Sarah McLachlan features a guest appearance by MUNA's Katie Gavin.
The latest full-length release Glasgow-based singer-songwriter Joanne Robertson features contributions by Oliver Coates.
The fourth full-length release from Brooklyn-based band Nation of Language was produced by Nick Millhiser.

The latest full-length release from Kentucky folk singer-songwriter Joan Shelley features contributions from Matt Kelley, Tamara Lindeman, Philippe Melanson, Karen Ng, Doug Paisley, Nathan Salsburg, Talya Bloom Salsburg, Ben Whiteley, and Ken Whiteley.
Neil Tennant appears on two songs on the latest live solo release from Johnny Marr that features tracks recorded from Marr's performance at London's Hammersmith Apollo in 2024.
The four-disc box set from the British alt-rock band The Wedding Present features 40 select album songs, B-sides and singles with sleeve notes by lead singer David Gedge.

The second full-length release from British rapper Kojey Radical features guest appearances by Bawo, Benjamin AD, Chrissi, Col3trane, Cristale, Dende, Ghetts, Jaz Karis, MNEK, Planet Giza, SOLOMON, and James Vickery.
The latest full-length solo release from Paris-based Lebanese singer-songwriter Yasmine Hamdan features contributions by Anas Alaili, Marc Collin and Omar Harb.
The latest full-length release from British pop singer-songwriter Ed Sheeran was recorded partly in India.
The latest full-length release from British indie artist Baxter Dury features a guest appearance by JGrrey and was produced by Paul Epworth.
The debut full-length solo release from Little Mix group member Jade Thirlwall includes contributions by Cirkut, Lostboy, MNEK, RAYE, Sabath, and Tove Lo.
This is the final album from Michael Hurley, who was often known as the "godfather of freak folk." He passed away in April 2025.
The debut full-length release from the British band Maruja was produced by Samuel W Jones and features elements of jazz, rock, punk and spoken word.
The latest full-length solo release from Gruff Rhys is entirely in Welsh and features backing vocals by Cate Le Bon and H. Hawkline.

album_title: I Can't Give Everything Away (2002 - 2016) [Box Set]
summary: The David Bowie 13 CD/18 LP box set includes remasters of 2022's Heathen, 2023's Reality and 2013's The Next Day Extra (2016's Blackstar and 2017's No Plan were not remastered); previously unreleased recording of the July 2002 performance at the Montreux Jazz Festival; remastered and re-sequenced release of A Reality Tour; 41 remastered rare tracks in Re:Call 6; and a hardback book.

album_title: I Believe In You, My Honeydew
summary: The latest full-length release from Brooklyn-based singer-songwriter Josh Ritter was produced by Sam Kassirer.

The latest full-length release from British pop singer-songwriter Sophie Ellis-Bextor features contributions by such artists as Selena Gomez, Kid Harpoon, Julia Michaels, MNEK, Nile Rodgers, Shura, and Sigrid.
The latest full-length release from Swedish pop singer-songwriter Jens Lekman is a concept album about the relationship between a wedding singer and his girlfriend.
This is the first full-length studio release from British post-punk band Chameleons since 2001's Why Call It Anything?
The third full-length release from New York artist King Princess features a guest appearance by Joe Talbot.
